{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"fields":{"slug":"/episode-7-the-one-where-we-become-friends/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Episode 7. The One Where We Become Friends","tags":["friendship","questions"],"date":"2020-02-03T13:00:00.000Z","category":"episode","imgsrc":"assets/dsc04851-2.jpg","link":"<iframe src=\"https://open.spotify.com/embed-podcast/episode/09fOFKxr38LX8Hr4WQwmSa\" width=\"100%\" height=\"232\" frameborder=\"0\" allowtransparency=\"true\" allow=\"encrypted-media\"></iframe>"},"excerpt":"<p>You asked, we answered! In our 7th episode, we answer all the questions!</p>\n<p>The three of us were…</p>","html":"<p>You asked, we answered! In our 7th episode, we answer all the questions!</p>\n<p>The three of us were friends way back before this podcast began, so this week we start with a story time of how we met. We talk about our first impressions of each other and then dive deep with questions for each other. Inspired by Mandy Len Catron’s <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2015/01/11/style/modern-love-to-fall-in-love-with-anyone-do-this.html\">essay</a> about the <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2015/01/11/style/36-questions-that-lead-to-love.html\">36 questions</a> that lead to love, we try to fall further into friendship love.</p>\n<p>Listen to the very end to hear us answer the questions YOU asked about heartbreak and insecurities.</p>","id":"e6b86df6-51df-512a-9dc9-f37da0b1b2b0"},"file":{"absolutePath":"/home/sloh/projects/moving-oolong/static/assets/dsc04851-2.jpg","relativePath":"assets/dsc04851-2.jpg","childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","placeholder":{"fallback":"data:image/jpeg;base64,"},"images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/bfdd5469a672b37d7afed69b3a2163e3/b8f93/dsc04851-2.webp","srcSet":"/static/bfdd5469a672b37d7afed69b3a2163e3/1f5b3/dsc04851-2.webp 841w,\n/static/bfdd5469a672b37d7afed69b3a2163e3/a399f/dsc04851-2.webp 1683w,\n/static/bfdd5469a672b37d7afed69b3a2163e3/b8f93/dsc04851-2.webp 3365w","sizes":"(min-width: 3365px) 3365px, 1